            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Waldo G. Leland, historian and editor, made many contributions to both the historical and archival professions. Of the many works which he wrote, edited, or compiled, his complete<emph render="italic"> Guide to the Materials for American History in the Libraries and Archives of Paris</emph> has proved a very useful tool for historians of French Colonial America. This collection contains materials photocopied by Leland which were to comprise Volumes III and IV of his <emph render="italic">Guide</emph>. The information was gathered between 1905 and 1942, and includes the Archives of the Ministeres de la Guerre, Comite Technique de l&#039;Artillerie, Comite Technique du Genie, Service Hydrographique, Ministere de la Marine, the Actes du Pouvoir Souverain, and the Archives Nationales, Section Moderne.</p>
                                 <p>The Library of Congress copied these items for the Illinois Historical Survey in 1974.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


